{"questionId":"22646420","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The hypotheses for Janneke’s test are</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:40px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>:</mo></math>&nbsp;the heights are drawn from a normally distributed population with mean <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>170</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math>&nbsp;and standard deviation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:40px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>:</mo></math>&nbsp;the heights are not drawn from a normally distributed population with mean <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>170</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math> and standard deviation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the degrees of freedom for this test.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22646420","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ2.4d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the degrees of freedom for this test.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}